{"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The catalog of all components provided by OUDS. It contains also "},{"code":"View","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" extensions and "},{"code":"ViewModifiers","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to apply tokens and styles on components and higher-level views."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Components are grouped in several categories, the same as the ones defined in the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Figma","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" design kit:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Actions"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" component are for example buttons. ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Navigations"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" group contains links, ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"inputs"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" group has checkboxes, radio buttons and switches, ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"layouts","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" groups is dedicated to things like dividers.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"You can get more details about them in the categories below:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Actions","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Navigations","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Inputs"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Layouts","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Customize components","anchor":"Customize-components"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Apply a specific shadow effect (elevation tokens)","anchor":"Apply-a-specific-shadow-effect-elevation-tokens"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The unified design system implemented by OUDS iOS library allows to apply "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"elevation effets"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" on a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View"},{"type":"text","text":", i.e. a shadow under the component."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Because the design tool in use is "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figma"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" which defines such shadow with a "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"blur","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" and a "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"spread","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" radiuses, and because "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"SwiftUI","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" uses only its own "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"radius","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" definition, an extension of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View"},{"type":"text","text":" has been implemented to let users apply some effect using an "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/elevationcompositesemantictoken"},{"type":"text","text":" from the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/"},{"type":"text","text":" library thanks to the method "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"shadow(elevation: ElevationCompositeSemanticToken)"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"code":["\/\/ For example, apply the elevation effect \"elevationDrag\" from your theme:","myView.oudsShadow(theme.elevations.elevationDrag)","","\/\/ And in the theme this \"elevationDrag\" has been defined for example like:","@objc open var elevationDrag: ElevationCompositeSemanticToken { ElevationCompositeSemanticToken(ElevationRawTokens.elevationBottom_3_500) }","","\/\/ And if you look deeper, the raw token \"elevationBottom_3_500\" can be like:","public static let elevationBottom_3_500 = ElevationCompositeRawToken(x: elevationX0, y: elevationY300, blur: elevationBlur400, color: ColorRawTokens.colorOpacityBlack320)","","\/\/ Blur will be used to compute the radius value"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Apply a specific typography (font tokens)","anchor":"Apply-a-specific-typography-font-tokens"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Your application identity can be strongly based on the ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"typography"}]},{"text":" you use, i.e. the font family you choose and other configuration details like the font size or the font weight.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With OUDS, typography depends to the class size, i.e. wether or not the application is in "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"compact mode"}]},{"type":"text","text":" or in "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"regular mode","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":", and is defined with a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/multiplefontcompositerawtokens","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". defined in the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/ios.unified-design-system.orange.com\/documentation\/oudstokenssemantic\/fontsemantictokens\/","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"theme","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" contains lots of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens"},{"type":"text","text":" listing all the combinations of typography you can apply, and these "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"composite semantic tokens"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" use "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"composite raw tokens","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":". For example:"}]},{"code":["\/\/ Here is a definition of a semantic token inside the theme for typography \"typeDisplayMedium\":","@objc open var typeDisplayMedium: MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens { ","MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens(compact: FontRawTokens.typeBold750, regular: FontRawTokens.typeBold1050) ","}","","\/\/ And here are the raw tokebs definitions:","public static let typeBold750 = FontCompositeRawToken(size: fontSize750, lineHeight: fontLineHeight850, weight: fontWeightBold)","","public static let typeBold1050 = FontCompositeRawToken(size: fontSize1050, lineHeight: fontLineHeight1150, weight: fontWeightBold)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"However the "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"theme","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" must know which "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"font family"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" to apply, and this font family can be a "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"custom one","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" or the "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"system one"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Thus, we let the users define the font family they want by overriding the "},{"code":"fontFamily","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" property. This value will be used to compute the typography, if not defined the systme font will be used."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Thus, if you want to apply a specific typography to a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View"},{"type":"text","text":", supposing you defined previously the semantic tokens, just call the method you want and gives as parameter the theme (to get the custom font if defined):"}]},{"code":["\/\/ Apply typography \"type body default small\"","myView.typeBodyDefaultSmall(theme)","","\/\/ Apply typography \"type label strong X large\"","myView.typeLabelStrongXLarge(theme)","","\/\/ Etc."],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Apply a specific border (border tokens)","anchor":"Apply-a-specific-border-border-tokens"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This module exposes the helper ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"oudsBorder(style:width:radius:color)"},{"text":" so as to apply border semantic tokens on a view in order to define a border effect.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The helper is available through ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View"},{"text":", and tokens through the provider of the theme.","type":"text"}]},{"code":["    @Environment(\\.theme) private var theme","","    var body: some View {","        SomeView()","        .oudsBorder(","             style: theme.borders.borderStyleDefault,","             width: theme.borders.borderWidthThin,","             radius: theme.borders.borderRadiusNone,","             color: theme.colors.colorBorderDefault)","     }"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Apply specific colors","anchor":"Apply-specific-colors"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Colors can be applied on view for background and foreground colors, foreground style or also accent color."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Some helpers are available in the OUDS API to avoid to use the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"color(for:ColorScheme)"},{"type":"text","text":" method."}]},{"code":["    \/\/ Given a color at theme.colors.colorBgPrimary","    \/\/ This token can have light and dark declinations ","","    @Environment(\\.theme) private var theme","","    \/\/ Apply a foreground style","    someView.oudsForegroundStyle(theme.colors.colorBgPrimary)","","    \/\/ Apply a foreground color","    someView.oudsForegroundColor(theme.colors.colorBgPrimary)","","    \/\/ Apply a background","    someView.oudsBackground(theme.colors.colorBgPrimary)","","    \/\/ Apply an accent color","    someView.oudsAccentColor(theme.colors.colorBgPrimary)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[[]]},"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"externalID":"OUDSComponents","symbolKind":"module","modules":[{"name":"OUDSComponents"}],"role":"collection","title":"OUDSComponents","roleHeading":"Framework"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Articles","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Actions","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Inputs","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Layouts","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Navigations"],"anchor":"Articles"},{"generated":true,"title":"Structures","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSButton","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckbox","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxIndeterminate","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItem","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSCompone